inputs.description: A collection of arguments for invoking getUsers.

nameRegex.description: Regex string to apply to the IAM users list returned by AWS. This allows more advanced filtering not supported from the AWS API. This filtering is done locally on what AWS returns, and could have a performance impact if the result is large. Combine this with other options to narrow down the list AWS returns.

pathPrefix.description: Path prefix for filtering the results. For example, the prefix `/division_abc/subdivision_xyz/` gets all users whose path starts with `/division_abc/subdivision_xyz/`. If it is not included, it defaults to a slash (`/`), listing all users. For more details, check out [list-users in the AWS CLI reference][1].

outputs.description: A collection of values returned by getUsers.

arns.description: Set of ARNs of the matched IAM users.

id.description: The provider-assigned unique ID for this managed resource.

names.description: Set of Names of the matched IAM users.
